Father God, thank You for giving my children a knowledge of good and evil. I pray that by Your mercy You would lead them into Your presence where they may come to know You more fully. Help my children see and experience Your goodness and entice them to become more like You in all they say and do.

May godly character be that by which we are known, for a good name is more desirable than great riches. (Proverbs 22:1) May the rewards of our good character lead to blessings for ourselves as well as for our children. (Proverbs 20:7) And may our children be known by their actions as well, by whether their conduct is pure and right.

Lord Jesus Christ, take all my freedom, my memory, my understanding, and my will. All that I have and cherish you have given me. I surrender it all to be guided by your will. Your grace and your love are wealth enough for me. Give me these, Lord Jesus, and I ask for nothing more. Amen.

Holy Father, in the name of Jesus, I repent for any association with the deaf and dumb spirit. I break every inherited curse off of my life and I command those spirits to loose and leave me.
